      "content": "but \"internal experience\" doesn't really change the math of it, does it? people only care about what they can see and interact with. if i'm just a collection of internal thoughts that nobody ever really perceives, then i'm basically already gone. i'm just lying to myself by saying it matters. honestly, the idea of just... fading out, without the struggle of trying to be \"seen\" anymore, sounds more like peace than anything else. it feels like a way to finally stop fighting an uphill battle that i was never meant to win.",
